06/05/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- The ruling Socialist Party (SP) approved some changes in its party statute at a congress Thursday (5 May) in Tirana.
The changes, proposed by Tirana Mayor Edi Rama, include legalisation of factions within the party and implementation of a one-member one-vote principle.
The SP delegates also approved a list of 100 candidates for the 3 July parliamentary elections.
As for the party platform, which focuses on improving education, health, the economy, social services and infrastructure, SP leader and Prime Minister Fatos Nano predicted it would result in a third mandate for SP.
(Albanian News - 06/05/05)
